hpnicfDHCPServerMib.name: hpnicfDHCPServerMib
hpnicfDHCPServerMib.description: This MIB describes objects used for managing DHCP server.

HpnicfDhcpSEnabledStatus.name: HpnicfDhcpSEnabledStatus
HpnicfDhcpSEnabledStatus.description: To descript the status of some function is Enabled or Disabled.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolTable.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolTable
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolTable.description: A table for creating DHCP server global pools.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolEntry
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolEntry.description: An entry containing objects for creating or deleting a global pool for the DHCP server.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolRowStatus.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolRowStatus
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigTable.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigTable
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigTable.description: A table containing the configurations of dhcp server global pools.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigEntry
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for configuring the network ip or host ip etc. to global pools for DHCP server.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolType.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolType
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolType.description: Type of a DHCP global pool. Any operations of this object will be bound with the operations of hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork, hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolHostIPAddr, or hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolHostHAddr. That means any operation of this object alone will be regarded as invalid operation.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork.description: Network ip of a DHCP global pool. To delete a configured network ip, please set hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag to 1.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolNetworkMask.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolNetworkMask
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolNetworkMask.description: Net mask of a DHCP global pool(network). The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolNetwork together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. When a network ip of a DHCP global pool was deleted, the net mask would also be deleted automatically, and no further operation needed.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolHostIPAddr.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolHostIPAddr
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolHostIPAddr.description: Host ip of a DHCP global pool. To delete a configured network ip, please set hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag to 2.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolHostMask.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolHostMask
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolHostMask.description: Net mask of a DHCP global pool(host) The SET operation to this object ought to be with the SET of hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolHostIPAddr together, and any SET operation alone to this object will be regarded as an invalid operation. When a host ip of a DHCP global pool was deleted, the net mask would also be deleted automatically, and no further operation needed.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolHostHAddr.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolHostHAddr
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolHostHAddr.description: Hardware address of a DHCP global pool(host). To delete a configured hardware address, please set hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag to 3.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigUndoFlag.description: Flag of undo operation for hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolConfigTable.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolParaTable.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolParaTable
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolParaTable.description: A table for configuring parameters to DHCP global pools.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolParaEntry.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolParaEntry
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolParaEntry.description: An entry containing the objects for the configurations of parameters of DHCP global pools.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseDay.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseDay
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseDay.description: Number of days of the lease.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseHour.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseHour
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseHour.description: Number of hours of the lease.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseMinute.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseMinute
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseMinute.description: Number of minutes of the lease.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseUnlimited.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseUnlimited
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolLeaseUnlimited.description: A flag denoting if the lease of a pool is unlimited.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPStri.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPString
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPStri.description: String of gateway ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip ip at a time.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPUndo.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPUndo
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolClientGatewayIPUndo.description: A gateway ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip of gateway router.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolClientDNSIPString.description: String of DNS server ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip at a time.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolClientDNSIPUndo.description: A DNS server ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip of DNS server.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNetbiosType.description: NetBios node type for DHCP clients.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPString.description: String of NetBios server ip addresses for DHCP clients. Since mostly 8 ip can be configured for a pool totally, so a string is defined to get or configure 8 ip at a time.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPUndo.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPUndo
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolClientNbnsIPUndo.description: A NetBios server ip address to delete. This object is only for deleting a given ip of NetBios server.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolIPInUseReset.name: hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolIPInUseReset
hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolIPInUseReset.description: Reset the auto binding ip of the given global pool for DHCP server.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionIPString.description: Ip string of an option. 1 to 8 ip addresses can be configured at most simultaneously.

hpnicfDHCPSGlobalPoolOptionRowStatus.description: RowStatus. Three actions are used: active, createAndGo, destroy.
